{
    "word": "Hostage",
    "definitions": [
        "A person given as a pledge or security for the performance of the conditions of a treaty or stipulations of any kind, on the performance of which the person is to be released."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "Your hostages I have, so have you mine; And we shall talk before we fight.",
        "He that hath a wife and children hath given hostages to fortune."
    ],
    "etymology": "[OE. hostage, OF. hostage, ostage, F. , LL. hostaticus, ostaticum, for hospitaticum, fr. L. hospes guest, host. The first meaning is, the state of a guest, hospitality; hence, the state of a hostage (treated as a guest); and both these meanings occur in Old French. See Host a landlord.]"
}